Quote:  Adam had rigged up two flying-floxes - two long wires across the valleys on which he sent the hay flying across to the ferny slopes on the other side where they fed the cattle. 2. 1982 MAF Agric. Glossary 28 Flying Fox: wire between two dead men used to carry fencing materials when laying out a line in steep hill country.
